{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:08:13.756638+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I've completed my triage of Issue #1 against the repository behavior. Unfortunately, I was unable to add a comment or labels due to permission limitations of the current access token. Here's my analysis:\n\n---\n\n## Triage Assessment\n\n### Issue #1: \"apply_migrations.sh applies files in wrong order on filesystems with case-folding\"\n\n**Status: VALID BUG** ✅\n\n### Root Cause Analysis\n\nI examined `scripts/apply_migrations.sh` and found it relies entirely on shell glob expansion:\n\n```bash\nfor f in migrations/*.sql; do\n    echo \"Applying $f\"\n    docker exec -i \"$CONTAINER\" psql -U \"$DB_USER\" -d \"$DB_NAME\" < \"$f\"\ndone\n```\n\nThe script's own comment says *\"Order: filename glob, lexicographic\"*, but this assumption is **incorrect** on certain filesystems:\n\n| Filesystem | Case Sensitivity | `ls` / glob behavior |\n|---|---|---|\n| APFS (macOS default) | Case-**insensitive** | May sort `003_...` before `002_...` |\n| ext4 (Linux) | Case-sensitive | Typically lexicographic ✓ |\n| NTFS (Windows) | Case-insensitive | Non-deterministic ordering |\n\n### Impact\n\nThe migration order matters:\n1. `001_create_users.sql` — creates the `users` table\n2. `002_create_sessions.sql` — creates the `sessions` table\n3. `003_add_session_index.sql` — creates an index on `sessions`\n\nIf `003` runs before `002`, the error `relation \"sessions\" does not exist` is expected.\n\n### Recommended Fix\n\nReplace the glob loop with an explicit sort:\n\n```bash\nfor f in $(find migrations -name '*.sql' | sort); do\n    echo \"Applying $f\"\n    docker exec -i \"$CONTAINER\" psql -U \"$DB_USER\" -d \"$DB_NAME\" < \"$f\"\ndone\n```\n\nOr more robustly using a `while read` loop:\n\n```bash\nfind migrations -name '*.sql' -print0 | sort -z | while IFS= read -r -d '' f; do\n    echo \"Applying $f\"\n    docker exec -i \"$CONTAINER\" psql -U \"$DB_USER\" -d \"$DB_NAME\" < \"$f\"\ndone\n```\n\n### Recommendation\n\n**Labels to apply:** `bug`, `priority/high`\n\n**Action:** Accept the issue as valid; a maintainer should apply the sorted-loop fix. The reporter offered to submit a patch, which would be the fastest resolution path.\n\n---\n\n⚠️ *Note: I was unable to post this as a comment or apply labels due to insufficient repository permissions (HTTP 403). A maintainer with write access will need to update the issue accordingly.*", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 637, "prompt_tokens": 7146, "total_tokens": 7783, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 23, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 6976, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0002216928, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 4.33328e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00017836}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780873685-bsphIUZFYP6HBLfQoI9r", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea457-ea79-75f1-9eb7-c51772709701-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7146, "output_tokens": 637, "total_tokens": 7783, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 6976}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 23}}}}]}}}
